<a name="Bennett"></a><b>Bennett, Jonathan. How to read minds in behaviour: A 
suggestion from a philosopher</b>. <a href="#top">Whiten (1991)</a>, pp. 97-108. 
<p>
Abstract: (from the chapter) described a procedure for deciding what mental content 
to attribute to an animal... the economy rule as advice; empirically equivalent 
results; thoughts about thoughts: preliminary tidying; desires to produce thoughts: 
a dilemma. 
