<a name="Schmidt & Marsella"></a><b>Schmidt, Charles F. and Stacy C. Marsella</b>. 
Planning and plan recognition from a computational point of view. <a href="#top">Whiten 
(1991)</a>, pp. 109-126. 
<p>
Abstract: (from the chapter) the possession of a symbol system is required in 
order to achieve the full semantics that are typically associated with the capacity 
to represent beliefs and goals; in order to explicate the sense in which this 
statement is true, we will focus on the possible role of such representations 
in the various models of planning and plan recognition that have been developed 
within AI (artificial intelligence). 
