<a name="Ristau"></a><b>Ristau, Carolyn A. Before mindreading: Attention, purposes 
and deception in birds?</b> <a href="#top">Whiten (1991)</a>, pp. 209-222. 
<p>
Abstract: (from the chapter) review my evidence suggesting that plovers exhibit 
purposeful behaviour; field studies were undertaken to investigate the plovers' 
use of 'injury feigning' or broken wing displays; 'injury feigning' is among the 
most intense of a repertoire of anti-predator behaviours... deception; attentiveness 
to the gaze of another. 
