<a name="Baron-Cohen"></a><b>Baron-Cohen, Simon. Precursors to a theory of mind: 
Understanding attention in others</b>. <a href="#top">Whiten (1991)</a>, pp. 233-251. 
<p>
Abstract: (from the chapter) consider some new evidence of joint attention-deficits 
in autism, and explore the possibility that a critical precursor in the development 
of a theory of mind lies in the infants' understanding of attention in others. 
